article.headline: Cal Poly 89, Menlo 43
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Dylan Royer and Chris Eversley scored 15 points each to lead Cal Poly to an 89-43 win against Menlo College on Saturday night. Brian Bennett added 14 points and Kyle Odister 10 for the Mustangs (3-3), who shot 57.4 percent (31 of 54) from the floor and made 10 of 17 3-point attempts. ChaRunn Jones scored 15 points for Menlo (2-8), a NAIA school in Atherton, Calif. Odister's 3-pointer gave Cal Poly a 28-5 lead midway through the first half. Menlo shot 19 percent from the floor en route to trailing 42-14 at the break. Eversley finished with eight rebounds and two steals.
